article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 46, Stephen F.Austin 45
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Justin Reynolds hit 1-of-2 free throws with 2 seconds left and Texas A&M-Corpus Christi edged Stephen F. Austin 46-45 Saturday. Garland Judkins led the the Islanders (8-13, 3-4 Southland) with 13 points and Demond Watt added 12. Jordan Glynn had 12 points and 13 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (12-6, 3-3). Jereal Scott scored 13 and Antonio Bostic 11. Down 45-43 after Glynn's layup with 2:35 to go, Texas A&M-Corpus Christi tied it on a layup by Watt layup with 46 seconds remaining. Stephen F. Austin then turned the ball over, and Reynolds was fouled by Glynn. Reynolds hit the first before missing the second. The Lumberjacks ended the first half with six straight points for a 21-16 halftime lead. They pushed their lead to seven in the second half before the Islanders put together a 15-0 run for their biggest lead, 31-23 with 11:10 to play.
